## Bandit Level 9 → Level 10

**Challenge:** The password for the next level is stored in the file data.txt in one of the few human-readable strings, preceded by several ‘=’ characters.

**Solution:**
```bash
 string data.txt | grep "="
```

**Explanation:** 
`strings` filterst out the human readable strings
`|` once previous command executed, move the data to next command
`grep` out of the few human readable commands the one starting with "=" is filtered out.


**What I learned:** Sometimes it is easier to pair multiple commands together to run as one rather then running them seperately.
